The paper deals with capacity regions of two-way communication channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers multi-user networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The concept of adaptation is also relevant in the fields of signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI), and the paper uses computable outer bounds, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper considers the Gaussian two-way interference channel, which is a topic in multimedia communication (cs.MM).
